Semantic Web
From iA wiki
See also: Vision | Artifical Intelligence | Internet | Data
Home Page: http://www.w3.org/2001/sw/ at W3C
Semantics is the branch of semiotics dealing with the study of meaning we attach to language. The Semantic Web will allow software to interact more efficiently without human intervention. The idea is based upon a set of standards for protocol for metadata.
The rich vision of the semantic web is an extension of the current web in which data is given meaning through the use of a series of technologies. The Semantic Web is the part of the web that allows for automated communication between machines on behalf of users. Rather than visit a search engine and crawl through a flat listing of possible matches, users
